description:
src/delivery.rs process_batch() calls crate::persona::get_private_key(pool, &username).await and, if signing fails, does:

    Err(e) => {
        tracing::error!(error = %e, "failed to sign request");
        mark_dead(pool, &delivery_id, &e.to_string()).await?;

The error string e.to_string() is stored in delivery_queue.last_error. If the private key loading path produces errors that include key material in their Display output (e.g., a PEM parse error that echoes the raw bytes, or a key file read error that includes file contents in the anyhow context chain), that material lands in the DB.

Similarly, tracing::error!(error = %e, ...) sends it to the log output.

Mitigation: audit get_private_key error paths to ensure no key bytes appear in error messages; sanitize error strings before storing in last_error.
